Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.61,0:00:05.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}From a different point of view, even an imposing\Nwall blocking your path is just a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.12,0:00:07.99,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A character from a mystery novel\Nthreatens the life of its author.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.99,0:00:09.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is this fiction, or non-fiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.70,0:00:11.16,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.16,0:00:12.79,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but\Nhas the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.79,0:00:14.63,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.91,0:01:48.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,How to Win at Horse Racing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.95,0:01:51.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Pro Football, 2006
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.77,0:01:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm being called!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.96,0:01:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.33,0:01:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Coming through!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.63,0:02:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.59,0:02:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems it's my turn. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.52,0:02:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Wait! Inspector!\N- Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.74,0:02:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sure seem to have a lot of free time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.99,0:02:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since we're here anyway, please let us help with the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.11,0:02:23.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, this brat might cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.74,0:02:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Inspector, what kind of case is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.52,0:02:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.30,0:02:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is the person who lived in this flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.79,0:02:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, age 65.{uso: probably edit to "Murako Saikawa, age 65?"}\NShe lived alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.09,0:02:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently she was a novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.32,0:02:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does the name sound familiar, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.92,0:02:46.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murako Saikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.97,0:02:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I seem to recall that long ago, there was a novelist by that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.88,0:02:58.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Murako Saikawa...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.48,0:03:01.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An incredible mystery novelist,\Nfamous for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.86,0:03:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Death was instantaneous, caused by\Na blow to the head with a decorative object.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.36,0:03:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what was determined\Nduring the investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.36,0:03:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she was murdered last night,\Napproximately between 7 and 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.37,0:03:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We might get a more accurate estimated time of death once the autopsy is concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.99,0:03:21.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who'd want to murder a famous mystery novelist, and why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.38,0:03:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the body was found by two people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name's Tono.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:36.39,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shun'ichi Tono (26)\NEditor at Labyrinth Publications
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.74,0:03:34.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I work at Labyrinth Publications,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and I was Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.39,0:03:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this is the block of flats' manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.39,0:03:40.40,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Keiso Murata (55)\NPearl Block of Flats Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.23,0:03:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name's Murata.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:43.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell us again exactly\Nhow you found the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.65,0:03:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, I went over\Nto pick up some documents.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:49.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I met up with her yesterday, we'd agreed I'd come by to pick them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.52,0:03:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, no matter how often I kept ringing the intercom, nobody came to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.92,0:03:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I felt that was kind of strange,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.61,0:04:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I asked the manager to use his key to open the door for me, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.33,0:04:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.39,0:04:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.63,0:04:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.83,0:04:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.81,0:04:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you were at Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s home yesterday, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:15.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I was there from early in the evening until around 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.83,0:04:19.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The estimated time of death was between 7 and 9.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.34,0:04:21.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you've got really great instincts!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.40,0:04:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's odd that you knew something was up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.06,0:04:27.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,just because nobody answered the intercom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really does sound strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.32,0:04:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's because a couple of days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.43,0:04:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei received this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.20,0:04:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A postcard...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.08,0:04:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.48,0:04:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the next piece I will be adding to my collection will be your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.92,0:04:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will come to take it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.12,0:04:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A death threat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.57,0:04:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was sent by a... Taniyoshi Ohebi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's read Ryo Orochiya.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.60,0:05:04.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ryo Orochiya? That's insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.35,0:05:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's this Ryo Orochiya?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.03,0:05:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a criminal mastermind,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.57,0:05:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s biggest novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.86,0:05:15.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A character from her novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.78,0:05:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The novelist was murdered by a character from her novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.12,0:05:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not!\NThat's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.63,0:05:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.00,0:05:25.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that does seem to be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a trick by the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.19,0:05:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He did it to confuse the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.13,0:05:32.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}To confuse the investigators?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.74,0:05:35.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But was that the only objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.94,0:05:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if you have an empty flat, we'd appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.32,0:05:42.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'd like to use it as a base of operations for our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.34,0:05:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.35,0:05:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:05:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.77,0:05:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you may have been the last person to see the victim alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.41,0:05:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you stay with\Nus for a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.97,0:05:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.78,0:05:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.49,0:06:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said the flat was locked, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.66,0:06:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose the killer left it locked last night, before escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.67,0:06:10.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, they could delay the time it took to find the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.92,0:06:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But from what I understand, in this block, each tenant gets two keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.86,0:06:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s two keys were found inside the flat, weren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.52,0:06:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did the killer have a copy of the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.26,0:06:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. That means there's a limited number of people who could've used such a key.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.43,0:06:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The editor who came to meet her might have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he could've had one made.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.99,0:06:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the manager has one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.01,0:06:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.79,0:06:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.79,0:06:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.17,0:06:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was Kawanaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, he just finished interrogating all the neighbours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently, a few days ago, the victim\Nand the manager had a very heated row.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.76,0:07:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They seem to be our main suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:08.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tono{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, who was visiting the victim up until the estimated time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.21,0:07:10.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And Murata{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10},\Nwho had a potential motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.79,0:07:14.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Furthermore, either of them could've had a copy of the key made.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, if either of them is the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.32,0:07:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then it's no coincidence that they were the ones who found the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By being the first to arrive,\Nthe killer could've come inside
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.21,0:07:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and got rid of any evidence he might've left the previous night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.66,0:07:32.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.70,0:07:42.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.48,0:07:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just remnants of ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.43,0:07:46.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} hated fresh ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.97,0:07:51.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She always said she couldn't\Nstand its bittersweet taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.32,0:07:56.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose she took all of the ginger from the sushi she ordered last night, and threw it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.57,0:07:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She ordered sushi for dinner last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.95,0:08:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, she asked me for it,\Nand I ordered it over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.43,0:08:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, we have the entire floor available for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.29,0:08:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please tell us everything that happened last night, in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.03,0:08:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.55,0:08:20.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If she threw it away last night,\Nthen it's been over half a day since.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.21,0:08:23.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In that case, most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.39,0:08:30.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed\Nbetween 7 and 9pm yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.85,0:08:36.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I arrived to see her at around 6:30pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though she wasn't doing it\Nprofessionally anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.74,0:08:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she still kept writing a lot of mystery novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were together for about an hour, talking about the possibility of publishing them all as a collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.33,0:08:52.00,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, Saikawa.\NAt the Pearl block of flats.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:53.83,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The usual order, for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The order arrived at around 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.09,0:09:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I had other business\Nto deal with, I left afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.22,0:09:06.23,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll come to pick up the documents\Ntomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.23,0:09:07.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.46,0:09:09.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If you'll excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.10,0:09:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around a quarter to 9, I met up with some friends in front of the station,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.06,0:09:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and stayed with them\Nuntil deep into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.06,0:09:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until deep into the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.37,0:09:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll confirm this with your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:31.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm perfectly aware that I'm a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would I do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.92,0:09:38.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a treasure\Namong mystery novelists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.46,0:09:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have a row with Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.01,0:09:44.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People must've misunderstood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.63,0:09:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be the case.\NEither way, tell me about last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.64,0:09:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in the manager's quarters the whole time. {unsure, please check –Putoずっと管理人室に。 It's about right. zutto would probably be interpreted "the whole time". -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.37,0:09:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was alone, so I don't have any witness to confirm it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.39,0:09:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The manager's hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.48,0:10:00.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key point is at 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.28,0:10:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From 7 to 8, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could've committed the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.28,0:10:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after 8, it could've been Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.19,0:10:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, split up and investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.34,0:10:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were told she ordered\Nsushi from here last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.39,0:10:21.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! How could I screw up this bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:23.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.13,0:10:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll pay for this for my entire life!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you explain what you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:30.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The squid and the octopus!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.93,0:10:31.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.93,0:10:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The squid and the octopus?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.48,0:10:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, in our restaurant, we don't include squid or octopus in our orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.54,0:10:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}\Nordered them, we always did,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because they were her favourite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But last night, I was careless and forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.62,0:10:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, was that it?\NI thought it was something serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.14,0:10:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course it was serious!\NIt was her last order!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:11:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.54,0:11:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just came to ask when\Nyou took the order to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.47,0:11:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.63,0:11:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took the order to her flat at 8,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but he didn't see Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} anywhere, and didn't hear her talk, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, she was already in the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.48,0:11:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.21,0:11:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.37,0:11:34.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't, editor-in-chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.43,0:11:35.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the editor-in-chief of Labyrinth Publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:46.21,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yasunobu Shimazaki (50)\NLabyrinth Productions Editor-in-Chief
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.21,0:11:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name's Shimazaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.74,0:11:46.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was told Tono is one of your suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.21,0:11:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.72,0:11:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He came to work for us,\Nspecialising in mystery novels,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.46,0:11:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because he admired\NSaikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s work so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.97,0:11:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even today, he was planning the\Npublication of a collection of her works!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.73,0:12:04.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A true fan of Murako Saikawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.88,0:12:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you familiar with Murako Saikawa's works?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.99,0:12:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not until this case came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.99,0:12:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, because\Nshe's been forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.81,0:12:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's precisely why he insisted her works should be published.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.21,0:12:22.08,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's tons of people who don't know the greatness of Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-sensei{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:25.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Original tricks, perfect composition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.09,0:12:30.19,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I want everyone in Japan to know of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.72,0:12:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I didn't think it'd sell well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.19,0:12:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our publisher{confirm term please –Puto} is in a precarious situation.{うちの経営は　いつも火の車です。経営 [けいえい] /(n,vs) management/administration/(P)/}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And publishing something with low sales expectations would only make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.34,0:12:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think we'd do it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.85,0:12:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was moved by his passionate desire\Nto make her happy during her final days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.12,0:12:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her final days?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.07,0:12:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The doctor said she had an incurable illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.26,0:12:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had, at most, half a year to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.53,0:12:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono is the one who'd regret Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s passing the most!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.71,0:13:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.81,0:13:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.10,0:13:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Beika Medical University. {the catalan didn't say Beika, but I'm hearing it in the jp so added it –Puto医大 [いだい] /(n) (abbr) medical university/medical school/med school/(P)/prolly good enough -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.66,0:13:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.17,0:13:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've got the autopsy results back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.50,0:13:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim's stomach contained rice and raw fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.18,0:13:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably the sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.94,0:13:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. And apparently she was killed an hour later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.94,0:13:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the order was taken to her at 8pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.66,0:13:38.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the estimated time of death would be around 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.16,0:13:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And as far as Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.94,0:13:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we've confirmed that he was with his friends the whole night, starting at a quarter to nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.96,0:13:49.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His alibi checks out?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.00,0:13:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My apologies for having suspected you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.86,0:13:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can leave now, if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.48,0:13:55.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad, Tono.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.10,0:13:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.46,0:13:57.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse me, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.17,0:14:00.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.12,0:14:03.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What? You saw him last night?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.27,0:14:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.08,0:14:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I had to make a delivery at a specific time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and that's when I saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.92,0:14:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was around 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.28,0:14:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,9pm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.99,0:14:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I like to drink a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.72,0:14:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one day, old Saikawa saw me sipping a bit in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.32,0:14:28.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she'd inform\Nthe management company.{She said she was gonna inform the block of flats' management companyterm is probably wrong. –Puto.管理会社に報告するとかって...。}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.25,0:14:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've gotta be joking, I'd get fired for sure if that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.17,0:14:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I went to visit her last night, to ask her to reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.32,0:14:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no matter how much I kept ringing the intercom, that old lady wouldn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.76,0:14:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you suspect me, show me the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.03,0:14:47.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.59,0:14:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stinks of alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.46,0:14:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll open the window, to bring in some fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:04.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course! There's another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.77,0:15:06.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And there's also that ginger...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.25,0:15:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Proof... Proof...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.08,0:15:20.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I figured out the killer's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.26,0:15:28.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I figured out the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.06,0:15:30.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But what was the motive?{LTIL: But why did that person... -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.23,0:15:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Among the things found at the crime scene, there's nothing that indicates Mr Murata{isn't it -shi? -uso} as the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.62,0:15:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's on the news now.\NIt's super-sensational.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.13,0:15:51.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They probably made a ton of cash off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.42,0:15:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Famous Novelist Gets a Death Threat from a Character in Her Novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:15:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} couldn't keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.86,0:16:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even revealed all the info about the postcard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.84,0:16:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of an ongoing investigation are supposed to be a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.53,0:16:07.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.62,0:16:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it the usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.99,0:16:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.45,0:16:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.79,0:16:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please call Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.46,0:16:33.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've solved everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.46,0:16:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi! Chiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.57,0:16:41.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the killer used an alibi trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.75,0:16:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An alibi trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.14,0:16:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's put the case's facts in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.59,0:16:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was killed\Nbetween 7 and 9pm yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.53,0:16:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it happened approximately one hour after she ate the sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.65,0:17:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Therefore, the approximate time of death is 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.68,0:17:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where the problem lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.59,0:17:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was that determined?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.16,0:17:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the sushi order\Nwas taken to her at 8pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.97,0:17:13.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but the sushi inside Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Nstomach wasn't necessarily {\i1}that specific sushi{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.35,0:17:16.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was another.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.64,0:17:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.55,0:17:20.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In addition to the order of sushi that was sent to her at 8pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.86,0:17:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} visited her,\Nhe also brought some sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.60,0:17:31.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} {\i1}actually{\i0} ate the sushi that Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} brought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.94,0:17:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't after 8, but at 6:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.08,0:17:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An hour later, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.88,0:17:45.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that point, digestion\Nstopped in the victim's stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would prove that she was killed an hour after she ate the sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.66,0:17:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} called the sushi restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.97,0:17:54.88,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The usual order, for one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:56.88,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thank you for your patronage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.88,0:18:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stored the sushi that arrived\Nat 8 inside a plastic bag,{jp: vinyl is a wasei-eigo}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.55,0:18:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,locked the door with a copy of the key,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.26,0:18:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to ensure the body\Nwasn't found immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.14,0:18:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and halfway through, he threw away the bag with the sushi and the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.64,0:18:13.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, he was able to set up\Nan alibi for 8:45 onwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.52,0:18:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He knew that sooner or later, an autopsy would reveal that she died an hour after eating sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.35,0:18:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And given the call to the sushi restaurant at 8pm...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.95,0:18:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naturally, we thought the time of death was 9pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.82,0:18:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a result of that, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who had an alibi for that time, would no longer be a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.19,0:18:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is to say, he used the autopsy that was intended to help solve the case, in order to set up an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.13,0:18:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.33,0:18:51.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, you made a mistake. The ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.81,0:18:54.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that ginger was from last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.64,0:18:58.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would've dried up long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.19,0:19:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But somehow, the ginger we found was still soft...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.44,0:19:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because last night, when you disposed of the sushi you ordered, you also disposed of the ginger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.07,0:19:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This morning, you realised your mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.99,0:19:13.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,asked Murata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to open the door for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when the manager wasn't looking,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.95,0:19:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you slipped that ginger into the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.24,0:19:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stop this! Where are you getting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.75,0:19:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gave her sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.33,0:19:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's obvious that Sensei ate the same sushi that was taken to her at eight!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.35,0:19:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, according to the autopsy,\Nwhat did they find in Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s stomach?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.06,0:19:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was sushi, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.90,0:19:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but more specifically?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.75,0:19:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.95,0:19:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rice, tuna, sea urchin,\Nflounder, squid, octopus...?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Squid and octopus?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.91,0:19:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.83,0:19:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, doesn't it sound strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:19:56.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.99,0:19:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.58,0:20:01.59,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, no! How could I screw up this bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.59,0:20:04.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The squid and the octopus!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.09,0:20:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He forgot them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.50,0:20:12.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew exactly the kind of sushi she would like, and therefore, didn't forget...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.26,0:20:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The squid and octopus that she loved so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.28,0:20:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were shocked that the restaurant owner forgot them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.06,0:20:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The autopsy you manipulated,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,ended up turning against you, and brought you to your doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.11,0:20:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.55,0:20:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the end of the line for you, Tono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.13,0:20:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beginning with Ryo Orochiya, every criminal that Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} created
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.58,0:20:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,accepted their guilt when\Nthey were caught, did they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.24,0:20:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did you do it, Tono?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.35,0:20:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei was ill, and had very little time left.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.33,0:20:51.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if she died from an illness,\Nshe would've done so as a forgotten novelist,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.37,0:20:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and nobody would have\Npaid any attention to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.39,0:20:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if she was murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.53,0:21:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and by a character from the novels she herself wrote at that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the media would make a big deal out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.15,0:21:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted the world to know who Murako Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.55,0:21:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you came up with that strange death threat, and caused all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.73,0:21:17.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever the motive, there's {\i1}never{\i0} a justification for murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for her sake, it was better...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.29,0:21:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you really do this just for Saikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.29,0:21:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this came out in the media, the collection of her works would sell a lot more,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.35,0:21:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the publisher would profit greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.08,0:21:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you consider that, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.04,0:21:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted Labyrinth Publications to continue working on mystery novels...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.89,0:21:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tono... God damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.46,0:21:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimazaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.42,0:21:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A person who truly loves mystery novels would {\i1}never{\i0} commit murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.54,0:23:31.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, they changed to a different manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.05,0:23:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.58,0:23:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A manager who spends the entire day drinking is in no condition to work properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.05,0:23:40.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Down it goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:47.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What about a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.44,0:23:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, if everybody\Nhas a red handkerchief,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.06,0:23:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there's no way to tell\Nwhich one's yours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:23:59.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? A notebook?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.74,0:24:00.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.92,0:24:03.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a bloodstain on the planner.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.04,0:24:17.01,Signs,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.33,0:24:22.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.33,0:24:22.08,Signs,Typesetting,0,0,0,,Names in Katakana
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.08,0:24:23.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What does your name mean\Nin kanji, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.90,0:24:27.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}kochôran
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.90,0:24:27.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}murinandai
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.90,0:24:27.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The ko from moth orchid,\N{kochôran}and the nan from {murinandai}unreasonable demand... {胡難}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.01,0:24:27.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
